if you changed your path in the bottom box, you have fucked up ur run on your computer.

Changed the Environment Values.

edit: please note in the first screenshot it says version _11 - it has since been changed to 12

And also one guy above mentioned that I type ‘localhost’ instead of wreckedcars.no-ip.biz as the server name?

[br][br][size=1]Posted on: February 06, 2009, 05:08:46 pm[/size][hr]H[quote=“Oo Java, post:5, topic:260751”]Ok, that wasn’t very well explained in your first post.

Do you have the second picture? Where it says something similar to “____scape is online”.

If you do, then try connecting to “localhost” as opposed to “wreckedcars.no-ip.biz”

If you don’t see something similar to “____scape is online” then tell me what it says.[/quote]

Do you run command that displays this:

so far i’ve:

typed localhost instead of wreckedcars.no-ip.biz (ip)
and switched the positions of the environmental variables <>

it still doesn’t work, anymore advice?
